title: Grateful Dead Live at Irvine Meadows on 1988-04-22
description: Mississippi Half Step-> Feel Like A Stranger-> Franklin's Tower, Minglewood Blues, Candyman, Queen Jane Approximately, When Push Comes To Shove, Let It Grow China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Louie Louie, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Space-> The Wheel-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> All Along The Watchtower-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Black Muddy River

reviews.review_text:
Great Show Found this show thru "This day in History" and immediately sent this to my Bro who is celebrating his 34th Bday...what better way to start than a nice "On the day that I was born" Half Step. Cheers Bro !!!

Very powerful He's Gone !!!

THIS SHOW WAS ABSOLUTELY ON-FIRE This show was a sign of the times and a exclamation point on the band being on a roll and where they are heading..The shakedown is on minglewood on and the highlight of the show just as I remember it that night LOUIE LOUIE...changed my life this show and that song gave me the shove in the right direction....I never heard a band bust out a cover like that whith such a drastic change and sooo smoothe and origional and rockin as well...What style. all the irvine shows rocked but this was one that stuck out allot...Thank You

Rested Up and ready to play.  Sounds like the band and Jerry shook off the East Coast run sickness and feeling better, nice opener.

Highlights: Space
Surge Late 80's is the peak of The Grateful Dead.
